SENIOR SUNDAY! @susiesseniordogs has some bunny they want you to meet!

Did some-bunny say Easter-Wabbit?! Meet 10 year old Mason! This senior fella is up for adoption at @animalhaven shelter in Manhattan, NYC. Mason's shelter story starts when he arrived back in January with his canine brother. Their former owner was too ill to care for them properly anymore. Sadly, Mason's brother - whom he was very bonded too - passed away. And while Mason is well cared for at the shelter, his retirement years are anything but ideal. He's lost his whole family and he doesn't know why life has changed so abruptly. Mason deserves the love of his very own person again and to live out his golden years in the comfort of a real home. 
@animalhaven wrote, "Mason is a big love bug. He’s pretty mellow and loves belly rubs. And a few times a day he will love for you to toss a tennis ball around with him. He also loves ear rubs and butt scratches too, and moans with enjoyment! 
At this point in his life, Mason would prefer to be an only pet in the home but has made a few doggy friends who were very low key in the past - he just prefers not to live with them. Our behavior team has taught him some basic commands like 'sit' and 'down,' which was easy because he loves food! Mason is on a venison diet and still needs to put on a few pounds so he will happily take any treats you want to dish out to him, including peanut butter Kongs and green apple slices!" Overall, Mason is very easygoing and loves to snuggle. It's not his fault he has found himself homeless for his retirement years and would be so grateful to anyone who gives him a second chance.

To adopt Mason, please visit him at @animalhaven shelter located at 200 Centre Street, New York, NY. Questions can be sent to dogsandcats@ah-nyc.org.

SENIOR SUNDAY! @susiesseniordogs wants you to meet Mr. Mike! Looking for a well behaved Best-Furry-Friend to adopt? Look no further than Mr. Mike! He's 8 years old and in the prime of his life. If you just read Mr. Mike's age and suddenly became disinterested - that's exactly why he is still up for adoption - simply because of his age. And it's silly! Because Mr. Mike is the total package, yet so many people can't see past that number. Mr. Mike is located in Vermont and hoping his big adoption day will come soon. There are so many adventures to be had and memories to make together! 
@allbreedrescue_VT wrote, "8 years old has never looked so good! Mr. Mike is a lab mix who arrived to All Breed Rescue in Williston, Vermont in early March. He was quite sad when he arrived, but we were able to find him a foster home where is he THRIVING!

Mr. Mike is a playful pup with other dogs, but is also content to lay in bed for most of the day. He has such a easy-going, mellow temperament that not much fazes him so he would likely adjust to almost any new home (maybe even with a cat!). Mike would likely enjoy children who would respect him by not jumping all over him or tugging on his tail. 
He is learning basic obedience commands so he will be on his best behavior in his furever home. For an older guy, Mike has embraced this new thing called 'snow' and has been caught on multiple occasions frolicking and sticking his whole face in the fresh powder! If you're looking for a go-with-the-flow, loyal companion please consider adding Mr. Mike to your family!

All Breed Rescue accepts applicants in the New England and New York area. All applicants must meet the dog in person before adopting (no transport)." To adopt Mr. Mike, please email allbreedvt@allbreedrescuevt.com for more information and to set up a meet and greet.

SENIOR SUNDAY! @susiesseniordogs wants to know: has Candy caught your eye?! This 12 year old sweet-tart is looking for her forever candy crush! Before getting rescued, little Candy lived a life of neglect. The final straw was when she fell off a balcony - likely because she could not see and she walked off the ledge while nobody was watching her. Thankfully, Candy was brought to @animalhaven shelter in Manhattan, NYC and received a whole lot of vet care. Candy is now up for adoption and ready to find a responsible forever home. This little senior sugarpop is looking for her equally sweet, special someone! 
Candy is completely blind but it does not hinder her ability to love one bit! She also has a few "old lady growths" but is otherwise OK. She weighs just 10 pounds. Candy's ideal home would be one that is filled with lots of quiet time to relax and simply hangout during the day. Candy does not need much other than a human who enjoys pampering old pups! She gets along with other calm and friendly dogs and cats - but a home without rambunctious toddlers would be best for Candy. She loves to eat and to be spoiled and would truly thrive in a doting home. 
If you wish to learn more about Candy, please visit her at @animalhaven shelter located at 200 Centre Street, Manhattan, NYC. Adoption hours are Tuesday through Sunday from 12 noon to 7PM. (@animalhaven currently has many senior dogs in their care who are looking for adopters, please visit the shelter and ask to meet with a senior!)

SENIOR SUNDAY! @susiesseniordogs has the BEST news! So excited to announce that 11 year old Stella was ADOPTED!!! This beautiful, elder borzoi found forever love in the twilight of her life. Senior dogs make wonderful companion pets and her new parents, Taylor and Matt, instantly recognized what a gem Stella is. They officially adopted her last weekend and miss Stella made the long road trip home with her new family - they even stayed in a hotel on their way back home! For over four months Stella had no adoption interest. But all thanks to one couple - who realized that age is truly just a number - Stella now gets to live out her life as a cherished family member. However much time Miss Stella has left on earth, the important thing is that when it comes time for her to leave this world she will always be so loved and forever remembered. 
Taylor wrote, "My husband and I saw Stella in early February and her face grabbed our hearts. She didn’t have much adoption interest due to her age and diabetes. I contacted her foster mom that same day about Stella and 3 weeks later my husband and I were planning a trip to pick her up and bring her home with us. 
Thanks to her former foster mom, Stella’s diabetes was under great control when we got her and is continuing to be managed well by my husband and me (Stella now has 2 veterinarians as her dog parents!). Stella is an amazing dog and has settled right into our home. She is our first senior dog adoption and we are so happy to have her in our home. She now has 3 whippet brothers and enjoys exploring the backyard with them. She is slowly warming up to them - they are younger than her and very silly. (Stella is very mature and not sure if she wants to partake in their shenanigans yet.) She is the sweetest dog and we are so happy to be her forever home."

SENIOR SUNDAY! Today, @susiesseniordogs has a story for us with a happy ending. "This summer we adopted Gertrude from the York County SPCA. I’ve always had dogs, but my husband has never had one. He says he’s a cat person. I thought a senior dog would be a great addition to our three cats, three turtles, and five kids. It would also be a great introduction to being a dog parent for my husband. 
I had been following the SPCA’s Facebook page and there Gertrude was. We took a ride to see her and it was closed! As we were leaving I was looking at their Facebook page for their hours and up popped a picture of her at an event they were having at that moment! So we drove over to meet her. She was all I had hoped for - sweet, gentle, a great walker. I put in our application for adoption and went to pick her up the next day. 
At age 12, she had been a stray. She eased right into our home. She gets along with the cats (she and our youngest cat make a great begging team) and kids and really everyone she meets. She’s been up to NY to visit family, had a trip to the beach, and loves going to the dog park. She’s also been back to the SPCA to visit for their fall festival. 
And my 'cat person' husband cooks her a homemade diet and has her on a great walking schedule. He still says he’s not a dog person, he’s a Gertrude person. 😊 -Shannon"
